attributes.title: Realistic Summer Sports Simulator
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael goes to the games in the PC indie game, Realistic Summer Sports Simulator. It's realer than 3-D.Try the realism for yourself.

attributes.title: Dead or Alive Xtreme 2
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael hits the beaches in Dead or Alive Xtreme 2 for the Xbox 360. Be warned. Things get extreme.

attributes.title: ShellShock 2: Blood Trails
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael learns the importance of teamwork in Shell Shock 2: Blood Trails for the Xbox 360. Apparently teamwork means not shooting your allies in the face. Who knew

attributes.title: Cassie's Animal Sounds
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael takes a casual stroll down to the farm in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Cassie's Animal Sounds. There's cows, and spiders, and dragons, oh my!

attributes.title: Surgeon Simulator
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Dr. Jones and Dr. Free attempt to save lives in Surgeon Simulator 2013. It's going to be a busy night at the morgue.

attributes.title: Millipede
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael plays pest control in Millipede, available in Centipede & Millipede for the Xbox Live Arcade.

attributes.title: Rockstar Table Tennis
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael and Jesper team up in Rockstar Table Tennis for the Xbox 360 to challenge the greatest Ping Pong player of all time, Jesper.

attributes.title: Serious Sam Double D XXL
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael and Gavin double down in Serious Sam DD XXL for the Xbox Live Arcade. Divorces are always so messy.

attributes.title: Hide the Fart
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael squeaks out as many as he can in the online flash game, Hide the Fart. It was someone else, I swear.

attributes.title: The Runner
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael runs his little heart out in the Xbox Live Inde Game, The Runner. Dem spikes.

attributes.title: Super Hexagon
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael continues his ongoing battle with shapes in the Steam game, Super Hexagon. Failure has never been so vivid.

attributes.title: Shark Attack
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael is brutally ripped apart and eaten by sharks in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Shark Attack. At least they aren't zombies...OH GOD, NO!

attributes.title: Runner 2
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael runs, jumps, blocks, bounces. and slides to his demise in the Xbox Live Arcade Game, Runner 2.

attributes.title: World's Hardest Game
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael attempts the online flash game, World's Hardest Game. It turns out it was pretty challenging.

attributes.title: Uproar!
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael patrols the streets and beats ass in the the Xbox Live Indie Game, Uproar!. We've got a code 4, here!

attributes.title: Aircraft RC
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael takes to the skies in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Aircraft RC. He takes to the ground a lot too.

attributes.title: Surgeon Simulator 2013: Steam Edition
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Dr. Jones and Dr. Free are back in the OR as they attempt a heart, double kidney, and brain transplant in Surgeon Simulator 2013 available on Steam. So sit back, relax, and enjoy the longest and most outrageous episode of Rage Quit ever made. The Drs. are in and it's about to get bloody.

attributes.title: Surgeon Simulator 2013: Ambulance & Space Missions
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Dr. Jones & Dr. Free are back to finish the job in the Ambulance and secret Space Missions in Part 2 of Surgeon Simulator 2013: Steam Edition. Boldly going where no surgeons have gone before.

attributes.title: Feeding Frenzy
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael dives into Fish Frenzy for the Xbox Live Arcade. It's a fish-eat-fish world down there.

attributes.title: Among the Sleep (Alpha)
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael cacks his pants and crawls for his life in the Indie Game, Among the Sleep (Alpha). This is why I always sleep with a night light on.

attributes.title: Happy Pong
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael plays a twist of the classic game "Pong", in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Happy Pong. There are no words.

attributes.title: Cat Mario
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael plays the highly requested and insanely frustrating online flash game, Cat Mario. Not even Gatomon would be prepared for this.

attributes.title: Get Your Cell Together
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael plays the Xbox Live Indie Game, Get Your Cell Together. Where's Osmosis Jones when you need him

attributes.title: Hotline Miami
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael heads back to the 80s and hits the beach in Hotline Miami. He's looking for money, murder, and a place to wear loafers without socks.Can't get enough of Hotline Miami Get the first ever hands-on playable experience of Hotline Miami 2, only at RTX 2013!

attributes.title: The Unfair Platformer
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael learns that sometimes life isn't fair in the online flash game, The Unfair Platformer. It's a kangaroo court.

attributes.title: Uncraft Me!
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael uncrafts his little heart out in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Uncraft Me! I would uncraft these honies all night...

attributes.title: Baby Maker Extreme 2
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael prepares for his future of child care in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Baby Maker Extreme 2. That baby is going places.

attributes.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's Decade Duels Plus
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael believes in the heart of the cards as he challenges (AH Community Member) Andrew/Mister Sir to Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's Decade Duels Plus for the Xbox Live Arcade. It's time to duel!

attributes.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's Decade Duels Plus Part 2
attributes.description: In this week's exciting conclusion, Michael and Andrew face off once again in Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's Decade Duels Plus for the Xbox Live Arcade. Who will bask in the glow of victory and who will spend an eternity in the darkness that is the Shadow Realm FIND OUT NOW!

attributes.title: Monkey Poo Flinger
attributes.description: In this week's Rage Quit, Michael flings more than just obscenities in the Xbox Live Arcade soon-to-be classic, Monkey Poo Flinger.

attributes.title: Hyphen (Demo)
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael slowly rotates his way through the demo version of the upcoming Indie Game, Hyphen. Colors and shapes, man. It's all about colors and shapes.

attributes.title: The Impossible Game Level Pack: Level 3
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael takes another yearly go at the now legendary Xbox LIve Indie Game, The Impossible Game Level Pack. How will Michael fair with the unknown danger of level 3 About as well as he did on the first 2.

attributes.title: The Binding of Isaac
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael delves into the twisted, bizarre, and deadly dungeons in The Binding of Isaac, available for Steam. From the guys that brought you Super Meat Boy, it's sure to get weird.

attributes.title: League of Evil
attributes.description: In this week's Rage Quit, Michael enters the world of the League of Evil. This'll end well.

attributes.title: Unicorn Makeout Mania
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael smooches his foes to death in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Unicorn Makeout Mania. This is not for the feint of heart.

attributes.title: Electronic Super Joy
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael ventures into the colorful, catchy, and extremely frustrating Steam Indie Game, Electronic Super Joy.

attributes.title: Pocketbike Racer
attributes.description: This week, Michael revisits an old friend in the Burger King game, Pocketbike Racer for the Xbox 360. He's almost creepier than King Ryan....almost.

attributes.title: Grand Theft Auto V
attributes.description: This week, Michael decides to take the day off and catch some much needed R&R in Grand Theft Auto V for the Xbox 360. Isn't life grand

attributes.title: Shadow Warrior
attributes.description: Michael embraces his inner samurai and slices his way through his enemies in Shadow Warrior for Steam.

attributes.title: Paper Sky
attributes.description: This week, Michael soars through the air in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Paper Sky. You never knew living as a piece of paper was so dangerous.

attributes.title: Distraction
attributes.description: This week, Michael spreads his little wings in the online flash game, Distraction. Hide your fruit, the birds are coming...

attributes.title: Boson X
attributes.description: Michael quantum jumps his way through the deadly, tricky, and trippy Boson X for the PC and Mac. If you thought it would be easy without spikes, wait until you get to the color red.

attributes.title: Snowboard 2D
attributes.description: This week, Michael enters the world of extreme sports in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Snowboard 2D. Yup. That's it. Just playing some sports.

attributes.title: Probably Archery
attributes.description: This week, Michael shows you that shooting a bow and arrow isn't as easy as it seems in Probably Archery.

attributes.title: Hotline Trail
attributes.description: This week, Michael gets frustrated and screams in space with Hotline Trail.

attributes.title: SpongeBob: Boat-o-Cross 2
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael takes a tour of Bikini Bottom with everyone's favorite yellow sea creature in the Nickelodeon flash game, SpongeBob SquarePants: Boat-o-Cross 2.

attributes.title: Killzone: Shadow Fall
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael shows you how to get around Sony's HDCP whilst he plays Killzone: Shadow Fall for the PS4. Next-gen is so realistic.

attributes.title: Hurdle Turtle 2
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael and Turtes leap for the finish in Hurdle Turtle 2 for the Xbox Live Indie Arcade. Watch out for the fireballs.

attributes.title: Farm Fury!
attributes.description: This week, Michael deals with farming and mice in this week's Rage Quit - Farm Fury!

attributes.title: Iron Axe
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael tests his might and mettle in the side scrolling dungeon adventure, Iron Axe, for the Xbox Live Indie Arcade. Beware of falling boulders.

attributes.title: Freestyle Football Trials
attributes.description: This week on Rage Quit, Michael practices the fundamentals of Footy in the Xbox Live Indie Game, Freestyle Football Trials. These athletes are out of this world.

attributes.title: Uncraft Me 2
attributes.description: Michael takes a stab at Uncraft Me 2 in this week's Rage Quit.
